{{ThisDateInRecentYears}}
{{Day}}

==Events==
*[[30 BC]] &amp;ndash; [[Augustus|Octavian]] (later known as Augustus) enters [[Alexandria]], [[Egypt]], bringing it under the control of the [[Roman Republic]].
*  [[69]] &amp;ndash; [[Batavian rebellion]]: The [[Batavians]] in [[Germania Inferior]] ([[Netherlands]]) revolt under the leadership of [[Gaius Julius Civilis]].
* [[527]] &amp;ndash; [[Justinian I]] becomes the sole ruler of the [[Byzantine Empire]].
* [[607]] &amp;ndash; [[Ono no Imoko]] is dispatched as envoy to the [[Sui Dynasty|Sui]] court in [[China]] (Traditional [[Japanese calendar|Japanese date]]: July 3, 607).
* [[902]] &amp;ndash; [[Taormina]], the last [[Byzantine]] stronghold in [[Sicily]], is captured by the [[Aghlabid]] army.
*[[1203]] &amp;ndash; [[Isaac II Angelus]], restored [[Eastern Roman Emperor]], declares his son [[Alexius IV Angelus]] co-[[emperor]] after pressure from the forces of the [[Fourth Crusade]].
*[[1291]] &amp;ndash; The [[Switzerland|Swiss Confederation]] is formed with the signature of the [[Federal Charter]].
*[[1492]] &amp;ndash; [[Ferdinand II of Aragon]] and [[Isabella I of Castile]] drive the [[Jew]]s out of [[Spain]].
*[[1498]] &amp;ndash; [[Christopher Columbus]] becomes the first [[European ethnic groups|European]] to visit what is now [[Venezuela]].
*[[1619]] &amp;ndash; First [[African]] [[Slavery in the United States|slaves]] arrive in [[Jamestown, Virginia]].
*[[1664]] &amp;ndash; The [[Ottoman Empire]] is defeated in the [[Battle of Saint Gotthard (1664)|Battle of Saint Gotthard]] by an [[Habsburg Monarchy|Austrian]] army led by [[Raimondo Montecuccoli]], resulting in the [[Peace of Vasvár]].
*[[1759]] &amp;ndash; [[Seven Years' War]]: The [[Battle of Minden]], an allied Anglo-German army victory over the [[ancien regime|French]]. In Britain this was one of a number of events that constituted the [[Annus Mirabilis of 1759]] and is celebrated as [[Minden Day]] by certain [[British Army]] regiments.
*[[1798]] &amp;ndash; [[French Revolutionary Wars]]: [[Battle of the Nile|Battle of the Nile (Battle of Aboukir Bay)]] &amp;ndash; Battle begins when a [[Royal Navy|British]] fleet engages the [[French Navy|French Revolutionary Navy]] fleet in an unusual night action.
*[[1800]] &amp;ndash; The [[Act of Union 1800]] is passed in which merges the [[Kingdom of Great Britain]] and the [[Kingdom of Ireland]] into the [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland]].
*[[1801]] &amp;ndash; [[First Barbary War]]: The [[United States|American]] [[schooner]] {{USS|Enterprise|1799|6}} [[Action of 1 August 1801|captures]] the [[Tripoli]]tan [[polacca]] ''Tripoli'' in a [[list of single-ship actions|single-ship action]] off the coast of modern-day [[Libya]].
*[[1820]] &amp;ndash; [[London]]'s [[Regent's Canal]] opens.
*[[1828]] &amp;ndash; [[Bolton and Leigh Railway]] opens to freight traffic.
*[[1831]] &amp;ndash; A new [[London Bridge]] opens.
*[[1832]] &amp;ndash; The [[Black Hawk War]] ends.
*[[1834]] &amp;ndash; [[Slavery]] is abolished in the [[British Empire]] as the [[Slavery Abolition Act 1833]] comes into force.
*[[1838]] &amp;ndash; Non-labourer slaves in most of the [[British Empire]] are emancipated.
*[[1840]] &amp;ndash; Labourer slaves in most of the [[British Empire]] are emancipated.
*[[1842]] &amp;ndash; [[Lombard Street Riot]] erupts in [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]], [[United States of America|USA]].
*[[1855]] &amp;ndash; First ascent of [[Monte Rosa]], the second highest summit in the Alps.
*[[1876]] &amp;ndash; [[Colorado]] is admitted as the 38th [[U.S. state]].
*[[1894]] &amp;ndash; The [[Sino-Japanese War (1894-1895)|First Sino-Japanese War]] erupts between [[Japan]] and [[China]] over [[Korea]].
*[[1902]] &amp;ndash; The [[United States]] buys the rights to the [[Panama Canal]] from [[France]].
*[[1907]] &amp;ndash; Start of [[Brownsea Island Scout camp|First Scout camp]] on [[Brownsea Island]].
*[[1914]] &amp;ndash; [[Germany]] declares war on [[Russia]] at the opening of [[World War I]]. The [[Swiss Army]] mobilises because of World War I
*[[1927]] &amp;ndash; The [[Nanchang Uprising]] marks the first significant battle in the [[Chinese Civil War]] between the [[Kuomintang]] and [[Communist Party of China]]. This day is commemorated as the anniversary of the founding of the [[People's Liberation Army]].
*[[1937]] &amp;ndash; [[Josip Broz Tito]] reads the resolution &quot;[[Manifesto]] of constitutional [[congress]] of KPH&quot; to the constitutive [[congress]] of KPH ([[Croatian Communist Party]]) in woods near [[Samobor]].
*[[1941]] &amp;ndash; The first [[Jeep]] is produced.
*[[1944]] &amp;ndash; [[Anne Frank]] makes the last entry in her [[diary]].
*  1944   &amp;ndash; [[Warsaw Uprising]] against the [[Nazism|Nazi]] occupation breaks out in [[Warsaw]], [[Poland]].
*[[1948]] &amp;ndash; The [[U.S. Air Force Office of Special Investigations]] is founded.
*[[1957]] &amp;ndash; The [[United States]] and [[Canada]] form the [[North American Air Defense Command]] (NORAD).
*[[1960]] &amp;ndash; [[Dahomey]] (later renamed [[Benin]]) declares independence from [[France]].
*  1960   &amp;ndash; [[Communist party|Communist]] [[Party of Independence and Work]] is banned in [[Senegal]].
*  1960   &amp;ndash; [[Islamabad]] declared as the [[federal capital]] of the [[Government of Pakistan]].
*[[1964]] &amp;ndash; The [[Belgian Congo]] is renamed the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo|Republic of the Congo]].
*[[1966]] &amp;ndash; [[Charles Whitman]] kills 16 people at [[University of Texas at Austin|The University of Texas at Austin]] before being killed by the police.
*  1966   &amp;ndash; Purges of intellectuals and imperialists becomes official [[People's Republic of China]] policy at the beginning of the [[Cultural Revolution]].
*[[1967]] &amp;ndash; [[Israel]] annexes [[East Jerusalem]].
*[[1968]] &amp;ndash; The coronation is held of [[Hassanal Bolkiah]], the 29th [[Sultan of Brunei]].
*[[1975]] &amp;ndash; [[Helsinki Accords|CSCE Final Act]] creates the [[Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe|Conference for Security and Co-operation in Europe]].
*[[1977]] &amp;ndash; Former [[U2 spy plane|Lockheed U-2]] pilot [[Francis Gary Powers]] crashes the news helicopter he is flying in Los Angeles
*[[1980]] &amp;ndash; [[Buttevant Rail Disaster]] kills 18 and injures dozens of train passengers in [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]].
*  1980   &amp;ndash; [[Vigdís Finnbogadóttir]] becomes the first democratically elected female [[President of Iceland|head of state]]
*[[1981]] &amp;ndash; [[MTV]] begins broadcasting in the United States and airs its first video, &quot;[[Video Killed the Radio Star]]&quot; by [[the Buggles]].
*[[1984]] &amp;ndash; Commercial [[peat]]-cutters discovers a the preserved [[bog body]] of a man, called [[Lindow Man]], at [[Lindow Moss]], [[Cheshire]], [[North West England]].
*[[1993]] &amp;ndash; The [[Great Flood of 1993]] comes to a peak.
*[[1995]] &amp;ndash; The first [[Victoria's Secret Fashion Show]] is held at the [[Plaza Hotel]] in [[New York City]].
*[[1996]] &amp;ndash; [[Michael Johnson (athlete)|Michael Johnson]] breaks the 200m world record by 0.30 seconds with a time of 19.32 seconds at the [[1996 Summer Olympics]] in [[Atlanta, Georgia]].
*[[2001]] &amp;ndash; An agreement is reached on the position of the minority [[Albanian language]] in the [[Republic of Macedonia]].
*  2001   &amp;ndash; [[Bulgaria]], [[Cyprus]], [[Latvia]], [[Malta]], [[Slovenia]] and [[Slovakia]] join the [[European Environment Agency]].
*  2001   &amp;ndash; [[Alabama Supreme Court]] [[Chief Justice]] [[Roy Moore]] has a [[Ten Commandments]] monument installed in the judiciary building, leading to a [[Glassroth v. Moore|lawsuit]] to have it removed and his own removal from office.
*[[2004]] &amp;ndash; A [[Paraguay supermarket fire|supermarket fire]] kills 396 people and injures 500 in [[Asunción]], [[Paraguay]].
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; The [[I-35W Mississippi River Bridge]] spanning the [[Mississippi River]] in [[Minneapolis, Minnesota|Minneapolis]], [[Minnesota]], collapses during the evening [[rush hour]].
*[[2009]] &amp;ndash; A [[2009 Tel Aviv gay centre shooting|shooting attack]] at the [[Israeli Gay, Lesbian, Bisexual and Transgender Association|Gay and Lesbian Association]] building in [[Tel-Aviv]], [[Israel]], results in the deaths of two people.

