*[[1871]] &amp;ndash; [[John Lester]], American [[cricket]]er (d. 1969)
*[[1885]] &amp;ndash; [[George de Hevesy]], Hungarian chemist, [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Nobel laureate]] (d. 1966)
*[[1881]] &amp;ndash; [[Otto Toeplitz]], German mathematician (d. 1940)
*[[1889]] &amp;ndash; [[Walter Gerlach]], German physicist (d. 1979)
*[[1891]] &amp;ndash; [[Karl Kobelt]], Swiss politician (d. 1968)
*[[1892]] &amp;ndash; [[Kinsan Ginsan]], Japanese identical twins who lived to ages 107 and 108, respectively.
*[[1893]] &amp;ndash; King [[Alexander I of Greece]] (d. 1920)
*[[1894]] &amp;ndash; [[Ottavio Bottecchia]], Italian cyclist (d. 1927)
*[[1900]] &amp;ndash; [[Otto Nothling]], Former Australian cricketer and rugby union footballer (d. 1965)
*[[1901]] &amp;ndash; [[Francisco Guilledo|Pancho Villa]], Filipino world boxing champion (d. 1925)
*[[1907]] &amp;ndash; [[Eric Shipton]], British mountaineer (d. 1977)
*[[1910]] &amp;ndash; [[James Henry Govier]], British artist (d. 1974)
*  1910   &amp;ndash; [[Walter Scharf]], American composer (d. 2003)
