==Deaths==
*[[30 BC]] &amp;ndash; [[Mark Antony]], Roman politician and general (b. 83 BC)
* [[371]] &amp;ndash; [[St Eusebius of Vercelli]], Italian bishop (b. 283)
* [[527]] &amp;ndash; [[Byzantine Emperor|Emperor]] [[Justin I]] (b. 450)
*[[1137]] &amp;ndash; King [[Louis VI of France]] (b. 1081)
*[[1227]] &amp;ndash; [[Shimazu Tadahisa]], Japanese warlord (b. 1179)
*[[1252]] &amp;ndash; [[Giovanni da Pian del Carpine]], Italian explorer (b. c.1180)
*[[1402]] &amp;ndash; [[Edmund of Langley, 1st Duke of York]], son of [[Edward III of England]] (b. 1341)
*[[1457]] &amp;ndash; [[Lorenzo Valla]], Italian humanist (b. c.1406)
*[[1464]] &amp;ndash; [[Cosimo de' Medici]], ruler of Florence (b. 1386)
*[[1541]] &amp;ndash; [[Simon Grynaeus]], German theologian (b. 1493)
*[[1546]] &amp;ndash; [[Peter Faber]], French [[Society of Jesus|Jesuit]] theologian (b. 1506)
*[[1557]] &amp;ndash; [[Olaus Magnus]], Swedish writer (b. 1490)
*[[1580]] &amp;ndash; [[Albrecht Giese]], German politician and diplomat (b. 1524)
*[[1589]] &amp;ndash; [[Jacques Clément]], French assassin of [[Henry III of France]] (b. 1567)
*[[1675]] &amp;ndash; [[Weetamoo]], sachem of Pocasetts, a band of the [[Wampanoag people|Wampanoag]] [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|Indians]] her death winding up the end of [[King Philip's War]] (b. 1635)
*[[1714]] &amp;ndash; Queen [[Anne of Great Britain]] (b. 1665)
*[[1787]] &amp;ndash; [[Alphonsus Liguori]], Italian founder of the [[Congregation of the Most Holy Redeemer|Redemptionist]] order (b. 1696)
*[[1795]] &amp;ndash; [[Clas Bjerkander]], Swedish meteorologist, botanist, and entomologist(b. 1735)
*[[1796]] &amp;ndash; [[Sir Robert Pigot, 2nd Baronet|Robert Pigot]], British army officer (b. 1720)
*[[1798]] &amp;ndash; [[François-Paul Brueys D'Aigalliers]], French admiral (killed in battle) (b. 1753)
*[[1807]] &amp;ndash; [[John Walker (lexicographer)|John Walker]], British lexicographer (b. 1732)
*[[1812]] &amp;ndash; [[Yakov Kulnev]], Russian general (killed in battle) (b. 1763)
*[[1851]] &amp;ndash; [[William Joseph Behr]], German writer (b. 1775)
*[[1866]] &amp;ndash; [[John Ross (Cherokee chief)|John Ross (aka. Kooweskoowe)]], Principal Chief of the [[Cherokee|Cherokee Nation]] (b. 1790)
*[[1903]] &amp;ndash; [[Calamity Jane]], American frontierswoman (b. 1853)
*[[1911]] &amp;ndash; [[Samuel Arza Davenport]], American politician (b. 1843)
*  1911   &amp;ndash; [[Edwin Austin Abbey]], American painter (b. 1852)
*[[1917]] &amp;ndash; [[Frank Little (U.S. Trade Unionist)|Frank Little]], American labor organizer (lynched) (b. 1879)
*[[1918]] &amp;ndash; [[John Riley Banister]], American cowboy and [[Texas Ranger Division|Texas Ranger]] (b. 1854)
*[[1920]] &amp;ndash; [[Bal Gangadhar Tilak]], Indian nationalist leader (b. 1856)
*[[1929]] &amp;ndash; [[Syd Gregory]], Australian cricketer (b. 1870)
*[[1938]] &amp;ndash; [[John Aasen]], American actor (b. 1890)
*[[1943]] &amp;ndash; [[Lydia Litvyak]], Soviet female [[flying ace]] (b. 1921)
*[[1944]] &amp;ndash; [[Manuel L. Quezon]], First President of the Philippine Commonwealth (b. 1878)
*[[1966]] &amp;ndash; [[Charles Whitman]], American mass murderer (shot by police) (b. 1941)
*[[1967]] &amp;ndash; [[Richard Kuhn]], Austrian chemist, [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Nobel Prize Laureate]] (b. 1900)
*[[1970]] &amp;ndash; [[Frances Farmer]], American actress (b. 1913)
*  1970   &amp;ndash; [[Otto Heinrich Warburg]], German physician and physiologist, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize Laureate]] (b. 1883)
*[[1973]] &amp;ndash; [[Gian Francesco Malipiero]], Italian composer (b. 1882)
*  1973   &amp;ndash; [[Walter Ulbricht]], German communist statesman (b. 1893)
*[[1974]] &amp;ndash; [[Ildebrando Antoniutti]], Italian Catholic cardinal (b. 1898)
*[[1977]] &amp;ndash; [[Gary Powers]], American spy plane pilot (b. 1929)
*[[1980]] &amp;ndash; [[Patrick Depailler]], French Formula 1 driver (b. 1944)
*  1980   &amp;ndash; [[Strother Martin]], American actor (b. 1919)
*[[1981]] &amp;ndash; [[Paddy Chayefsky]], American writer (b. 1923)
*[[1989]] &amp;ndash; [[John Ogdon]], British pianist (b. 1937)
*[[1990]] &amp;ndash; [[Norbert Elias]], German sociologist (b. 1897)
*  1990   &amp;ndash; [[Graham Young]], British serial killer (b. 1947)
*[[1996]] &amp;ndash; [[Frida Boccara]], French singer (b. 1940)
*  1996   &amp;ndash; [[Tadeus Reichstein]], Polish chemist, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize Laureate]] (b. 1897)
*  1996   &amp;ndash; [[Lucille Teasdale-Corti]], Canadian physician and international aid worker (b. 1929)
*[[1997]] &amp;ndash; [[Sviatoslav Richter]], Ukrainian pianist (b. 1915)
*[[1998]] &amp;ndash; [[Eva Bartok]], Hungarian-born actress (b. 1927)
*[[1999]] &amp;ndash; [[Nirad C. Chaudhuri]], Indian-born writer (b. 1897)
*[[2001]] &amp;ndash; [[Korey Stringer]], American football player (b. 1974)
*[[2003]] &amp;ndash; [[Guy Thys]], Belgian football coach (b. 1922)
*  2003   &amp;ndash; [[Marie Trintignant]], French actress (b. 1962)
*[[2004]] &amp;ndash; [[Philip Hauge Abelson|Philip Abelson]], American physicist, (b. 1913)
*[[2005]] &amp;ndash; [[Al Aronowitz]], American music journalist (b. 1928)
*  2005   &amp;ndash; King [[Fahd of Saudi Arabia]] (b. 1923)
*  2005   &amp;ndash; [[Constant Nieuwenhuys]], Dutch painter (b. 1920)
*  2005   &amp;ndash; [[Wim Boost|Wibo]], Dutch cartoonist (b. 1918)
*[[2006]] &amp;ndash; [[Jason Rhoades]], American installation artist (b. 1965)
*  2006   &amp;ndash; [[Bob Thaves]], American cartoonist (b. 1924)
*  2006   &amp;ndash; [[Iris Marion Young]], American feminist and political scientist (b. 1949)
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; [[Tommy Makem]], Irish folk singer (b. 1932)
*[[2008]] &amp;ndash; [[Harkishan Singh Surjeet]], Indian politician (b. 1916)
*[[2009]] &amp;ndash; [[Corazon Aquino]], Former President of the Philippines (b. 1933)
*[[2010]] &amp;ndash; [[Lolita Lebrón]], Puerto Rican nationalist (b. 1919)
*  2010   &amp;ndash; [[Eric Tindill]], New Zealand rugby and cricket international player and referee/umpire (b. 1910)
