{{ThisDateInRecentYears}}
{{Day}}

==Events==
*   [[8]] &amp;ndash; [[Roman Empire]] [[General officer|general]] [[Tiberius]] defeats [[Dalmatia]]ns on the river [[List of rivers of Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bathinus]].
* [[435]] &amp;ndash; Deposed [[Patriarch of Constantinople]] [[Nestorius]], considered the originator of [[Nestorianism]], is exiled by [[List of Byzantine Emperors|Roman Emperor]] [[Theodosius II]] to a [[monastery]] in [[Egypt]].
* [[881]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Saucourt-en-Vimeu]]: [[Louis III of France]] defeats the [[Vikings]], an event celebrated in the poem ''[[Ludwigslied]]''.
*[[1492]] &amp;ndash; [[Christopher Columbus]] sets sail from [[Palos de la Frontera]], [[Spain]].
*  1492   &amp;ndash; The [[Jew]]s of [[Spain]] are expelled by the [[Catholic Monarchs]].
*[[1527]] &amp;ndash; The first known letter from [[North America]] is sent by [[John Rut]] while at [[St. John's, Newfoundland and Labrador|St. John's]], [[Newfoundland and Labrador|Newfoundland]].
*[[1645]] &amp;ndash; [[Thirty Years' War]]: the [[Battle of Nördlingen (1645)|Second Battle of Nördlingen]] sees [[France|French]] forces defeating those of the [[Holy Roman Empire]].
*[[1678]] &amp;ndash; [[Robert LaSalle]] builds the ''[[Le Griffon]]'', the first known ship built on the [[Great Lakes]].
*[[1783]] &amp;ndash; [[Mount Asama]] erupts in [[Japan]], killing 35,000 people.
*[[1811]] &amp;ndash; First ascent of [[Jungfrau]], third highest summit in the [[Bernese Alps]] by brothers Johann Rudolf and Hieronymus Meyer.
*[[1852]] &amp;ndash; First [[Harvard-Yale Regatta|Boat Race]] between [[Yale University|Yale]] and [[Harvard University|Harvard]], the first American intercollegiate athletic event. Harvard won.
*[[1860]] &amp;ndash; The [[New Zealand land wars|Second Maori War]] begins in [[New Zealand]].
*[[1900]] &amp;ndash; The [[Firestone Tire|Firestone Tire &amp; Rubber Company]] is founded.
*[[1913]] &amp;ndash; A major labour dispute, known as the [[Wheatland Hop Riot]], starts in [[Wheatland, California|Wheatland]], [[California]].
*[[1914]] &amp;ndash; [[World War I]]: [[Germany]] declares war against [[France]].
*[[1916]] &amp;ndash; World War I: [[Battle of Romani]] &amp;ndash; Allied forces, under the command of [[Archibald Murray]], defeat an attacking [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman army]] under the command of [[Friedrich Freiherr Kress von Kressenstein]], securing the [[Suez Canal]] and beginning the Ottoman retreat from the [[Sinai Peninsula]].
*[[1923]] &amp;ndash; [[Calvin Coolidge]] is sworn in as the 30th [[President of the United States]] in the early morning following the death of [[Warren G. Harding]] the previous day.
*[[1934]] &amp;ndash; [[Adolf Hitler]] becomes the supreme leader of [[Germany]] by joining the offices of [[President]] and [[Chancellor]] into ''[[Führer]]''.
*[[1936]] &amp;ndash; [[Jesse Owens]] wins the 100 meter dash, defeating [[Ralph Metcalfe]], at the [[1936 Summer Olympics|Berlin Olympics]].
*[[1940]] &amp;ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Kingdom of Italy (1861-1946)|Italian]] forces begin the [[Italian conquest of British Somaliland|invasion of British Somaliland]].
*[[1948]] &amp;ndash; [[Whittaker Chambers]] accuses [[Alger Hiss]] of being a [[Communism|communist]] and a [[secret agent|spy]] for the [[Soviet Union]].
*[[1949]] &amp;ndash; The [[National Basketball Association]] is founded in the [[United States]].
*[[1958]] &amp;ndash; The [[Nuclear energy|nuclear]] [[submarine]] {{USS|Nautilus|SSN-571|6}} travels beneath the [[Arctic Ocean|Arctic]] ice cap.
*[[1960]] &amp;ndash; [[Niger]] gains independence from [[France]].
*[[1972]] &amp;ndash; The [[United States Senate]] ratifies the [[Anti-Ballistic Missile Treaty]].
*[[1975]] &amp;ndash; A privately chartered [[Boeing 707]] crashes into the mountainside near [[Agadir]], [[Morocco]], killing 188.
*[[1977]] &amp;ndash; The United States Senate begins its hearing about [[Project MKULTRA]].
*[[1981]] &amp;ndash; [[Senegal]]ese opposition parties, under the leadership of [[Mamadou Dia]], launch the [[Antiimperialist Action Front-Suxxali Reew Mi]].
*[[1997]] &amp;ndash; [[Oued El-Had and Mezouara massacre]] in [[Algeria]]; a total of 116 villagers killed, 40 in Oued El-Had and 76 in Mezouara.
*[[2001]] &amp;ndash; The [[Real IRA]] [[3 August 2001 Ealing bombing|detonates a car bomb]] in [[Ealing]], [[London]], [[UK]] injuring seven people.
*[[2004]] &amp;ndash; The pedestal of the [[Statue of Liberty]] reopens after being closed since the [[September 11 attacks]].
*[[2005]] &amp;ndash; President [[Maaouya Ould Sid'Ahmed Taya]] of [[Mauritania]] is overthrown in a [[military coup]] while attending the funeral of [[King Fahd]] in [[Saudi Arabia]].

