==Campaigns around extreme poverty==
*[http://www.livebelowtheline.com Live Below the Line] - this campaign challenges people in developed countries to feed themselves with the equivalent of the extreme poverty line to raise awareness of the challenges faced by those trapped in the cycle of extreme poverty, and raise funds for organisations working against global poverty. This campaign was started by the [http://www.globalpovertyproject.com Global Poverty Project] and [http://www.theoaktree.org Oaktree Foundation] and launched in 2010. 
*[http://www.worldvision.com.au/ourwork/solutions/40hourfamine.aspx 40 Hour Famine] - World Vision Australia started the 40 Hour Famine in 1975, for the purpose of raising money to help children, their families and communities in desperate need.  The funds raised each year by the 40 Hour Famine continue to support World Vision’s work tackling the causes of poverty, through both short term solutions and long term development projects.


